article:
As of 13 December 2011, there were 555 National Wildlife Refuges in the United
States. Refuges that have boundaries in multiple states are listed only in the
state where the main visitor entrance is located. The newest refuge established
is the Cherry Valley National Wildlife Refuge in
Pennsylvania.[http://www.fws.gov/refuges/news/cherryValleyNWR.html]
